gin:10px 0">In every previous cycle (the gray/white lines), Bitcoin would r=
ip to a new ATH, then crash 75-85% and stay brutally underwater for 300=E2=
=80=93700+ days. We=E2=80=99re talking multi-year bear markets with soul-cr=
ushing lows like $198 (2015), $3,135 (2018), and $15,460 (2022).</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin:10px 0">The orange line (current cycle since the May 2026 $82,2=
00 ATH) started similarly but then diverged hard. Instead of following the =
pack lower, it bounced back strongly and is sitting at roughly -35% around =
day 200 =E2=80=94 while every prior cycle was already at -50% to -70%+ and =
still falling.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">It simply hasn=E2=80=99t follo=
wed the script. No catastrophic 70-80% drawdown. No multi-year death march.=
 The old halving-driven 4-year rhythm that everyone expected appears broken=
=2E</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Bitcoi=
n has matured. Bigger money, ETFs, Sa=
ylor and other institutional adoption seem to have changed the game. The be=
ar market still hurts, but it=E2=80=99s a completely different animal this =
time.</p><p></p></div></td></tr>
